* Helper class with data necessary recover a single application key, given a recovery key. * *
    *
  • Alias - Keystore alias of the key. *
  • Encrypted key material. *
* * Note that Application info is not included. Recovery Agent can only make its own keys * recoverable. * * @hide

variables.name: mEncryptedKeyMaterial
variables.comment: The only supported format is AES-256 symmetric key.

variables.name: mMetadata
variables.comment: The optional metadata that's authenticated (but unencrypted) with the key material.

methods.name: public String getAlias()
methods.comment:
* Application-specific alias of the key.
     *
     * @see java.security.KeyStore.aliases

methods.name: public byte[] getEncryptedKeyMaterial()
methods.comment: Key material encrypted by recovery key.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(Parcel out, int flags)
